---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import DownloadButtons from '../components/DownloadButtons.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Setup - Aventura">
  <div class="relative flex min-h-screen w-full flex-col overflow-x-hidden">
    <Header currentPath="/setup" />

    <main class="flex-1 flex flex-col items-center w-full">
      <!-- Header -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 md:py-16">
        <h1 class="text-text-cream text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-medium leading-tight tracking-tight">
          Setup
        </h1>
      </section>

      <!-- Step 1: Download -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">1. Download</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body mb-6">
          <p>Get Aventura for your platform.</p>
        </div>
        <DownloadButtons compact />
      </section>

      <!-- Step 2: Choose Provider -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">2. Configure an AI provider</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body mb-8">
          <p>When you first launch Aventura, you'll need to set up an AI provider. There's built-in support for:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><a href="https://openrouter.ai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">OpenRouter</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://nano-gpt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">NanoGPT</a></li>
            <li>Any OpenAI-compatible API endpoint</li>
          </ul>
          <p>You can change providers or add custom endpoints later in Settings.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-border-brown/50">
            <img src="/start-openrouter.png" alt="OpenRouter setup" class="w-full" />
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-border-brown/50">
            <img src="/start-nanogpt.png" alt="NanoGPT setup" class="w-full" />
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-border-brown/50">
            <img src="/start-custom.png" alt="Custom API setup" class="w-full" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Step 3: Create Story -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">3. Create a story</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p>The setup wizard will guide you through creating your first story:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li>Choose a mode (Adventure or Creative Writing)</li>
            <li>Pick a genre template or start from scratch</li>
            <li>Create your protagonist</li>
            <li>Configure your world settings</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Tips -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Tips</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Start with a template</span> - It helps you learn how the system works before creating custom worlds.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Use checkpoints</span> - Save before major story decisions so you can explore different paths.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Build your lorebook</span> - Adding characters and locations helps the AI stay consistent.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
